    {
      "key": "ai_2",
      "display_name": "get duplicate vendors",
      "connector_key": "ai",
      "action_key": "generic_ai",
      "input_config": {
        "control": "object",
        "value": {
          "user_prompt": {
            "control": "text",
            "value": "Perform vendor matching for the vendor name: ${steps.ai_3.response.name}\n\nand output their name and  guid. if there are more then 4 limit the output to just 4\n\nhowever if this guid matches any of the above, remove that one from the results and do not mention it in the output: ${steps.trigger.request.vendor.id}\n\n\n"
          },
          "tools": {
            "control": "multipicklist",
            "value": [
              "zip_data"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "branches": null,
      "error_handling_policy": 1,
      "connection_var_key": null
    },
    {
      "key": "ai_3",
      "display_name": "normalize name",
      "connector_key": "ai",
      "action_key": "generic_ai",
      "input_config": {
        "control": "object",
        "value": {
          "tools": {
            "control": "multipicklist",
            "value": []
          },
          "user_prompt": {
            "control": "text",
            "value": "AI Step — Normalize & Resolve Parent/Owner (Procurement-Relevant)\n\nGoal:\nNormalize the vendor name and, only when relevant to procurement, return the actual legal entity that would be the contracting/billing vendor.  and cases where the input is an acronym (e.g., “EY”) or has missing/extra spaces (e.g., “Homedepot” vs “Home Depot”).\n\nInputs:\nvendor_name: ${steps.zip_1.vendor.name}\ncontact_email (optional): ${steps.zip_2.contacts[0].email}\n\nProcess\n\nNormalize & Generate Candidate Variants\n- Lowercase the vendor name.\n- Trim leading/trailing spaces and collapse internal whitespace to single spaces.\n- Remove punctuation and business suffixes (inc, llc, ltd, corp, co, company, etc.).\n- Jurisdiction-aware suffixes: recognize and remove: cc (ZA/Namibia/Botswana), pty ltd (ZA/AU), bv (NL), gmbh (DE/AT/CH), srl/sl (IT/ES), sp z o.o. (PL), sa/sas (FR/ES/RO), plc (UK/IE), oy (FI), ab (SE), as (NO/EE), kft (HU), sro (CZ/SK), a.s. (CZ/SK), etc. If present, set `jurisdiction_hint` accordingly.\n- Acronym handling: If input matches a known vendor acronym/alias (e.g., ey → ernst & young, pwc → pricewaterhousecoopers), add the expanded variant to the candidate set.\n- Whitespace variants: If normalized value becomes a single merged token plausibly representing a compound name (e.g., homedepot), add split-space candidates (e.g., home depot).\n- If email is provided, extract domain and eTLD+1 (e.g., atlassian.com) and add the domain-owner name (if obvious from domain) to the candidate set.\n\n"
          },
          "model": {
            "control": "picklist",
            "value": "auto"
          },
          "output_format": {
            "control": "picklist",
            "value": "structured"
          },
          "structured_schema": {
            "control": "array",
            "value": [
              {
                "control": "object",
                "value": {
                  "key": {
                    "control": "text",
                    "value": "name"
                  },
                  "description": {
                    "control": "text",
                    "value": "vendor name after applying rules"
                  },
                  "type": {
                    "control": "picklist",
                    "value": "string"
                  }
                }
              },
              {
                "control": "object",
                "value": {
                  "key": {
                    "control": "text",
                    "value": "reason"
                  },
                  "description": {
                    "control": "text",
                    "value": "reason behind decision"
                  },
                  "type": {
                    "control": "picklist",
                    "value": "string"
                  }
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "branches": null,
      "error_handling_policy": 1,
      "connection_var_key": null
    },
    {
